                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign></seg></handNote></handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                      Decorative designs: <locus target="#1r #7v #22v #31r #37v #42v #50r #59v #66v #81r #92r #102r #113v #120r" facs="002 009 024 032 039 044 051 061 068 082 093 103 115 121">folss. 1r, 7v, 22v, 31r, 37v, 42v, 50r, 59v, 66v, 81r, 92r, 102r, 113v, 120r, </locus> (ḥaräg);
                      <locus target="#14v #71r #96v #113r" facs="016 072 098 114">14v, 71r, 96v, 113r, </locus>, a line of full stops between lines of alternating red and black dots;
                      <locus target="#89v" facs="091">89v</locus>, lines of alternating red and black dots
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a1"><desc type="OwnershipNote"><locus target="#132v" facs="134">Fol. 132v</locus>Concluding prayer, including name of owners, Wäldä Mika’el and Wälättä Iyasus. </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a2"><desc type="GuestText"><locus target="#132v" facs="134"> f. 132v, column 2, lower (later hand)</locus>: Excerpt from Image of Roqo (identity of Roqo is unknown)</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e1"><desc><locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso)" facs="001 002">Fols. ir(ecto), iv(erso)</locus> pen trials</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e2"><desc><locus target="#55r" facs="056">Fol. 55r</locus> a small red and black cross in the margin marks the midpoint of the Psalms</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e3"><desc><locus target="#133r" facs="134">Fol. 133r</locus> the text is badly effaced and illegible</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e4"><desc><locus target="#133v #134r" facs="135">Fols. 133v, 134r</locus> blank</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e5"><desc><locus target="#134v" facs="136">Fol. 134v</locus> scrawl</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e6"><desc>
                        words of text are written interlinearly, <locus target="#12v #21r #28v #31r" facs="014 022 030 032">folss. 12v, 21r, 28v, 31r, </locus>, etc.;
                        and lines of text are written interlinearly, <locus target="#7r #10v #11r #52v" facs="008 012 012 054">7r, 10v, 11r, 52v, </locus>, etc.;
                        erasure markings are visible, <locus target="#26v #28r" facs="028 029">26v, 28r, </locus>;
                        text has been removed, e.g., <locus target="#6v #11v #17r" facs="008 013 018">6v, 11v, 17r</locus></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e9"><desc>The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection
                        of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes
                        the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout)</desc></item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
